text:
tahun 2017 pengaduan korban kekerasan berbasis gender ke lbh apik jakarta mencapai 648, diantaranya 308 kasus kekerasan dalam rumah tangga (kdrt), 37 kasus kekerasan seksual dan 30 kasus kekerasan dalam pacaran (kdp). pada kasus kdrt, dan kdp ada bentuk kekerasan seksual, sehingga secara menyeluruh kasus kekerasan seksual mencapai 94 kasus.

kasus kekerasan seksual yg mengemuka pada tahun 2017, adalah kasus perkosaan dan pencabulan, banyak dialami korban anak perempuan (31 kasus). hanya 11 kasus kekerasan seksual yang menimpa anak diproses hingga ke pengadilan sedangkan korban perempuan dewasa lebih sedikit lagi yakni 6 kasus.

hal ini karena tidak ada peraturan perundangan yang khusus mengatur kekerasan seksual.

ayo dukung dan sebarkan kampanye #gerakbersama dalam rangka 16 hari anti kekerasan terhadap perempuan.

ikuti dan sukseskan bersama gerakan masyarakat untuk pengesahan ruu penghapusan kekerasan seksual, jakarta 08 desember 2018 jam 08:00 wib @parkiransarinah

text:
@cocoloveblossom and kate spataro, our learned guides, last weekend here in #victoriabc co-facilitating the wheel of consent. there are a handful of times i've felt this seen, understood, and held.. i wish this feeling for the planet and all its willing inhabitants. a tearful, joyful, soul-full thank you wonderful humans for providing this opportunity for us.
.
.
i am a student in a programme called somatic sex education, (as well as sexological bodywork) currently mid-way in part three of five.
.
.
dr. betty martins wheel of consent has been the most crucial of my studies. finding my voice and feeling in my power enough to use it after thirty-some-odd without has been pivotol in my journey to unravel trauma's hold so far. i am a survivor of childhood sexual abuse, adult sexual abuse, addiction to drugs and alcohol, mental illness and witnessed my entire generation give a giant middle finger to the patriarchy. so, i can proudly say this work is #healingasfuck.
.
.
consequently, it's become clear this is a cornerstone of my offering to you, my audience. developing inner awareness and empowering your choice and voice through physical activities that tune us into our bodies is the key.
.
.
an example; has someone ever offered you a massage? they enthusiastically ask, "hey babe, how about a nice shoulder rub?" to which you may have said, "oh ma gosh yes please! my shoulder blades are tight."
.
.

.

inside, you're like, "what the *&#$, i thought you were massaging my shoulders? um..."
.

.
.

name: Claire
tweet_full:
@cocoloveblossom and kate spataro, our learned guides, last weekend here in #victoriabc co-facilitating the wheel of consent. there are a handful of times i have felt this seen, understood, and held.. i wish this feeling for the planet and all its willing inhabitants. a tearful, joyful, soul-full thank you wonderful humans for providing this opportunity for us.
.
.
i am a student in a programme called somatic sex education, (as well as sexological bodywork) currently mid-way in part three of five.
.
.
dr. betty martins wheel of consent has been the most crucial of my studies. finding my voice and feeling in my power enough to use it after thirty-some-odd without has been pivotol in my journey to unravel trauma's hold so far. i am a survivor of childhood sexual abuse, adult sexual abuse, addiction to drugs and alcohol, mental illness and witnessed my entire generation give a giant middle finger to the patriarchy. so, i can proudly say this work is #healingasfuck.
.
.
consequently, it is become clear this is a cornerstone of my offering to you, my audience. developing inner awareness and empowering your choice and voice through physical activities that tune us into our bodies is the key.
.

.......anonymous✨

text: let’s talk more about anxiety...do people question why you are blowing things out of proportion? or maybe they say stop over reacting! but let me tell you this...if you have anxiety...then you know how real it really feels! these thoughts make us feel the world is going to end in that moment, or like the worst is going to happen...there is confusion and frustration that comes out with it at times...we are scared, emotional, mad, overwhelmed, jumpy, etc. i’m sure it’s frustrating and annoying to be the partners of people like myself, but what we need is your support, love, and reassurance when it seems like a pointless reaction from us. thank you to those who have loved me through it, especially my daughter and husband. you continue to be patient with me and remind me it’s okay. ❤️

text: | bridging the g a p | often, people ask why we provide our shelter clients with new clothing instead of gently used clothing. it is a great opportunity to educate our community about health disparities. health disparities are preventable differences in the burden of disease, injury, violence or opportunities to achieve optimal health that are experienced by socially disadvantaged populations (cdc.gov). that means a person’s race, income, zip code, disability, sexual orientation, immigrant status and more can completely prevent them from accessing the amazing wellness tools northeast ohio has to offer. if a survivor makes the courageous decision to leave their abuser and find shelter, most of their possessions are left behind. or, financial abuse and/or little income prevent them from having many in the first place. shelters are a temporary, necessary, amazing solution to the long-term problem of healing after abuse. most things are borrowed or secondhand, so tough as milk gives them their portable peace package (sports bra, top, pants, yoga mat) new to symbolize their new chapter. something to say they deserve wellness, yoga, healing and it’s not just for the elite and extra-bendy. in true eco-fashion, the outfits are worn many times and something they take with them once they leave shelter. i encourage us in the wellness space to acknowledge our privilege and hopefully find a small way to make these wonderful health tools more accessible to all. collaborating/supporting nonprofits like frontline service, cleveland domestic violence and child advocacy center, @thecitymission , esperanza, @jfsacleveland and many more, not just for holidays, but throughout the year to ensure that all who can benefit from these services are included. everyone has a story and needs a helping hand at some point or another, you never know who you’ll help. 💛
name: Tough as Milk

i have scars that most people don’t know about. life hasn’t always been easy but i don’t regret my past. i wouldn’t be the person i am today without them.
a setback is not a reason to stop. setbacks are powerful lessons that test your faith, grow your confidence and make you a stronger person. learn from the lesson and get back on track. 
i accept my past, i am grateful for my present and i am filled with gratitude that i have a future to look forward to. it is a privilege to grow old. 📸 : @chris_pantera

text: :::37::: these 3 poems are what i randomly opened to on the day of my birth. it speaks to where i’m at in this life journey. the healing i’ve done, the work i continue to do. it’s not easy. this year has been hard and heavy. i’m changing. and with that change, i’ve stretched, screamed, and cried more times than i dare admit. i’m speaking my truth. it’s coming out with a roar that some days is shaped like sadness, other days like anger. it’s okay. because the work is not only changing my life, but the lives of three little hearts that call me momma. cheers to the start of another trip around the sun, the winter season, rooting down, shedding, and coming back stronger. 💕❄️ #gratitude #mindfulmedicine #yungpueblo #soulfood #growth #metoo #selfcare #thebodykeepsthescore

text:
remember....
"the gift of being broken open...
and there is beauty in the brokenness.
it is a beauty of constellations in the scars, of tides in the tears,
the heat of fire in the bleeding of you.
in the abrupt quiet that follows an unexpected injury, a sacred silence fills you.
and because there is nothing left in you that can create, push, force, be, or drive into, there is a blessed empty space, to be filled by something other than all the crazed and busy thinking, the manic achieving, and the over-scheduled hours.

this blessed, beautiful brokenness is the prayer that summons the spirit,
calls forth the angels, lays us down gently.
in these seasons of humble brokenness, we are opened, utterly.
there is no protecting yourself here.
this is the stripping away of ego-driven, striving conception.

let there be grace.
let there be mercy.
allow the broken places to show you their beautiful rest.
the broken stick on the forest floor is the branch who earned her rest.
i bless the stick.
i bless the rest."
~sarah la rosa, from 'beautiful broken things'

text:
i am not the shame you created. 
i am not the broken you instilled so deeply. 
little did you know, you created us. you created the unbreakable system that would go on to validate others. love others. and slowly, learn to love myself again...every single part. 
you thought you broke me. you thought i wouldn’t survive. 
but i did. 
and now, because of you, i know my strength. i know my power. 
and i will never give up. 
this is just the beginning. 
#survivor

text:
free weaving workshop 
this sunday 9 december
4pm to 6pm 
katherine hot springs. 
all materials provided for you to create your own basket. 
happy weaving terri xx

i am weaving today to commemorate the
16 days of activism against gender based violence that commenced on 25 november, the international day for the elimination of violence against women and ends of 10 december international human rights day.

ragbag women acknowledges the horrific and devastating impact of gender based and sexual violence in our community.

i will be relaxing with the wild women weaving at my favourite place, katherine hot springs to weave, reflect and strengthen the united community voice that violence plays no part in our community. 
you are welcome to join our weaving group as a peaceful stand to say no to violence in our community

happy peaceful weaving
terri

text:
"one day,  i was travelling home from school with my younger brother by bus in my school uniform. a man was sitting behind me and he tapped me. when he tapped me, i turned around and looked at him. as soon as i looked at him, he exposed a private part of his body to me inappropriately. to be honest, i was very small and i cried a lot, so i walked towards the front of the bus. an uncle saw that i was crying and asked me why. when i told him what happened, he asked another passenger who was getting off at the same place to take me home safely. then that person dropped my brother and me home. at that time, i got really scared. since i was so small, i was not sure how to react. i am sharing my experience now, because then hopefully other girls can be vigilant and aware when travelling in public transport. sri lanka is a country where many people use public transport. i hope that other people can understand how they must use public transport when they hear my experience, and i hope the relevant authorities will take necessary action to address this issue when they hear my story" - ronali
.

if you witness sexual harassment in public transport: intervene. speak up. be the change.
.
පොදු ප්‍ර‍වාහනයේදී ලිංගික හිංසනයක් දුටුවොත් කතා කරන්න. මැදිහත් වන්න ඔබ ම වෙනස වන්න.
.
பொதுப்போக்குவரத்தில் பாலியல் துன்புறுத்தல் நடைபெறுவதை நீங்கள் பார்க்க நேரிட்டால் இடையிடுங்கள், துணிந்து பேசுங்கள், மாற்றமே நீங்களாகுங்கள். .
© eliza hatch / cheer up luv for unfpa
.

"one day,  i was travelling home from school with my younger brother by bus in my school uniform. a man was sitting behind me and he tapped me. when he tapped me, i turned around and looked at him. as soon as i looked at him, he exposed a private pa of his body to me inappropriately. to be honest, i was very small and i cried a lot, so i walked towards the front of the bus. an uncle saw that i was crying and asked me why. when i told him what happened, he asked another passenger who was getting off at the same place to take me home safely. then that person dropped my brother and me home. at that time, i got really scared. since i was so small, i was not sure how to react. i am sharing my experience now, because then hopefully other girls can be vigilant and aware when travelling in public transpo. sri lanka is a country where many people use public transpo. i hope that other people can understand how they must use public transpo when they hear my experience, and i hope the relevant authorities will take necessary action to address this issue when they hear my story" - ronali

text:
🌷 “human rights are women’s rights and women’s rights are human rights, once and for all.” —hillary clinton 🌷

text:
as i’ve begun receiving submissions to the survivor tree project, i’m starting to realize what it means that people are trusting me with these narratives. what it means that i’m being given the most vulnerable and intimate parts of people, laid absolutely bare. reading these submissions is humbling, transcribing them is religious, and doing this work has dredged up a million other emotions i can’t come close to expressing. i want to hold you and cry with you and tell you that i’m sorry for what you’ve been through and that things will be better now. i can’t do that. and it aches. but know this: i will do my very best to honor you. to transcribe these words and do this work with as much love and care and tenderness as i have in my heart. to protect your stories and believe you and amplify you. you deserve that, and so much more. but the least i can give you is my transparency. to be as raw with you as you have been with me, and allow you to get to know this person that you have trusted with these delicate parts of you. i know i do not owe you (or anyone) that, but i want to give it to you, if you’ll have it. so allow me to reintroduce myself: my name is melinda- mel for short. i’m 33, and i currently live in new orleans where i work as a pastry chef. i am many things: among them, a sci-fi/comic book nerd, a tattoo enthusiast, a dog mom, a traveler, a sister, a foodie, a black indigenous woman of color, an artist, and a multiple rape and sexual abuse survivor. •

over the course of the next week, i’ll be re-transcribing my experiences on three different leaves, and i will subsequently be sharing those stories here. as i post them (with trigger warnings), i’ll be publishing them in my ig highlights as well. read them or don’t read them- it doesn’t matter. the reason they’re there is for you to know that you’re not alone and that you’re real and you can be alive after what happened to you. there is so much that is here for you. ✨🌱 #survivor #survivoradvocate #survivorselfcare #rapesurvivor #metoo #timesup #whyididntreport #endrapeculture #believewomen #believesurvivors #believeblackwomen #biwoc #artist #workinprogress #wip #thesurvivortreeproject

#orangetheworld

this year’s theme, #hearmetoo, aims to amplify the voices of survivors, to listen to, to believe survivors, to end the culture of silencing and impunity, and to put survivors at the centre of the conversation and response.

let’s stand with survivors for they must be heard, believed and supported.

illustration by @fatimah.creates

in a post #metoomovement world, this conversation is even more important. many critics think that #metoo is done kind of controversy. why have all these #women be silent for so long. the truth is we have been enduring for many years. finally, someone had the courage to speak up, allowing the rest of us the courage to speak up too. in the words of #oprah, #timeisupnow!. this isn't new or unknown. these are the realities we have always lived by, but fear of not being believed, of being put under the microscope, where your life is scrutinised, fear of being isolated and forget marginalised, thinking to yourself that you are over thinking something, fear of being deemed a bitch, fear of being dubbed as being unreasonable and so much more has always held women back from speaking up. but more than that, it is being dismissed and made in to be a liar that so many of us would shut up than report.
through my #16daysofaction, against #violenceagainstwomen, it has been a reminder that i must speak up. i hope you will too.

text: today has been hard... not so much with trauma stuff directly. i tend to cope by focusing and attempting to control my food and what i eat. focusing on what i eat and the number going down on the scale is much easier than the bigger stuff. but trauma stuff feels at an okay place right now. super triggered with ed thoughts (for purposes of this account i’ll call them that). i’ve struggled with ed before, but i think now i’m just more in a disordered relationship with eating. anyways, the last few days i was so motivated to have a better relationship with food and eat intuitively. i’m back to being so scared and i feel like i’ve gained weight. that’s really scary for me. i think i’m going to weigh myself in the morning. haven’t worked out much either, gotta get back at that. change is hard. but gonna focus on the fact that i’m trying to work through this #ptsd stuff and sometimes the ed is just so intertwined that it is tricky... i’m rambling i know. sending lots of love to everyone ❤️ oh and a shout out to revelatori, who i adore!!

text:
traumatic events by definition, overwhelm our ability to cope. it can take you years to actually face what has happened. and numerous more to overcome it.
when the mind becomes flooded with emotion, a circuit breaker is thrown that allows you to survive the experience reasonably ‘intact’. that is, without becoming psychotic or frying out one of the brain centres. 
the cost of this blown circuit is emotion frozen within the body. we often unconsciously stop feeling our trauma partway into it, like a movie that is still going after sound has been turned off, we disassociate. 
being able to survive doesn’t mean it was all ok.
there are wounds that never show on the body, that are deeper and more hurtful than anything that bleeds. 
you feel changed by trauma and it is tempting to think the changes are permanent. they are not. 
trauma creates change you don’t choose. healing creates change you do choose.

text:
paranoid or prepared: that game we all play when we think we're being followed.
.
this is a weird place to do this, but i dont have a lot of platforms, so here we are. ladies, what are ways you're out there being safe? comment on this post whether you follow me or not. maybe we can help other women one way or another.
.
i feel like mhk is a safe place for the most part. tonight, i left the union (i was studying) earlier than i would have liked because i saw it was getting dark. a man was walking his dog the opposite direction as me. when i passed him he turned around. he followed me to the opposite side of campus, crossed the street no more than 5 feet behind me, turned the same direction as me, then turned the same direction as me again down an empty, poorly lit street. at the first street i made a wolverine hand with my keys. at the first same turn i sped up. at the second same turn i was practically jogging. i walked slowly up the stairs to my apartment to make sure he didn't know which was mine. was he a malevolent man out to hurt me? probably not. did that prevent me, a fairly large woman, from being scared anyway? of course not.
.
i've learned ponytails are easy to grab, phone calls prevent you from hearing, and the handle on my hydroflask make it easy to hold in a casual yet defensive position. i try to stay in the streetlight's rays, carry a small pocketknife in my backpack, and i always walk quickly. what have you learned? what has your mama taught you?
.
to the ladies: it happens everywhere. to all of us. continue to live your life, but please. be safe.
to the men: i don't think all men are evil or violent. i have a great deal of male friends who would drop everything to walk me home if i told them i was uncomfortable. the worst thing you could do as a result of this post is become angered, and the best thing you could do is realize i am not alone in this terrible, high risk game.

.

.
i wish christians were among the loudest to agree with the concept that women are not sex objects for men's satisfaction. sadly i have seen too many threatened over it. i can't help but believe it is another missed opportunity to show deep compassion for other people.

text:
i’m proud of myself today. i went for it on my latest blog post on “7 statements on early sexual trauma & the impact on adult relationships”. this was almost to the line of where i’d consider not sharing, but i went for it. as much of an open book i am, i do hold back on some topics. i asked myself “what do i have to lose?” and when i came up with nothing, i went for it. •
•
early sexual violence, coercion and even consensual experiences that happen at a young age have a deep effect on how we behave sexually as adults. my biggest fear is that my daughter will have similar experiences and it will rob her of the joy that can be shared during intimacy. •
•
i debated not smiling during this post because umm we are talkin sexual trauma here.. but i’m not the one who shouldn’t be smiling. he shouldn’t be smiling. so i’ll continue to smile. •
•
if you’re curious about how early sexual trauma impacted me, check out my blog post under the mental health section, link in my bio! •
•

text:
"nobody deserves your tears, but whoever deserves them will not make you cry" - gabriel marcia marquez

this quote perfectly sums up one of our favorite #bts images of adrienne. adrienne is one of the four survivors who will be featured in the inaugural volume of survivor series. a loving mom to a spicy toddler (or princess depending on the day), disney kid for life, survivor of multiple rape/assaults and a fierce political advocate for survivors - choosing adrienne to be in this series was a no brainer. whether it be reciting depositions at the pennsylvania capital building or educating her social media followers about sexual assault/rape, adrienne is a force to be reckoned with and we're happy to have caught this small moment of vulnerability and strength.

these aren't tears of defeat or sadness, but of love and hope for the impact this series will have on other survivors. these tears were a rally cry.

to follow adrienne's journey as a survivor, check out her page at @adriennnneleigh 📸 by @bertaamelin
.
.
.

🚨heyo peeps with vaginas, this is a psa. i know you’ve heard a million times that you shouldn’t ever wear tampons. that if they’re not organic tampons, they are usually doused with chemicals which your vagina absorbs. that if they are organic, they’re still not great for you. to quote my gynecologist, “wearing tampons doesn’t let the normal clots and clumps of blood to be released from your vagina, as they can’t be absorbed. in addition to that, if you are keeping the shed blood in your vagina for long periods of time, you’re allowing bacteria to grow. this could possibly cause at least, bacterial vaginosis. it could also cause tss”. toxic shock syndrome could cause anything from a mild fever to death. also limb amputation. (yes it’s rare.) •
•
but this isn’t really about tampons. it’s about jade eggs. you’ve heard of them - right? popularized by @gwynethpaltrow and #goop it’s a trend where women stick polished crystal “eggs” up their vagina to tighten it. have i sold it to you yet? no? well, let me quote @goop - “concubines used them to stay in shape for emperors”. hey - what’s more appealing than using something which some old man’s sex-puppet used to keep herself in a tight shape for his royal dick? we’re all for #femaleempowerment over here.
•
•
oh, jade eggs also “cultivate sexual energy, balance the cycle, prevent uterine prolapse, intensify female energy, clear chi pathways in the body, invigorate your life force” cure cancer, solve global warming, send men to the moon, etc. obviously all this has been proven by the medical community who spent years upon years studying the human body...but you know, who cares about the medical community, if an actress who sells you “energy stickers for your body” tells you to sick rose quartz up your vagina, you do it!! cause ya know, #easternmedicine from la and stuff. •
•
using a #jadeegg to balance #yoni #hormones is biologically impossible, but you probably already realized that. jade (or rose quartz), is porous and could allow bacteria to get inside, and could cause bacterial vaginosis & #tss. but, i’m not a doctor. so talk to a doctor you trust. ask about kegels & tampons. and don’t listen to goop.

text:
some companies have reconsidered the “holiday party” event due to recent harassment cases.
movements like #metoo #niunamas are bringing issues to light that people never discussed before.
but... here is my problem, as a company if you choose to:
- cancel your holiday party
- limit drink options - invite limited staff

text:
transparency tuesday | as open, honest and transparent as i am about my journey, i’ve had the hardest time opening up about my weight...the numbers on the scale. 258 lbs is the most i’ve ever weighed in my life🤦🏽‍♀️ the lowest i’ve ever weighed in my adult life was 172 lbs back in 2005. at the time, i was a stay at home mom living in the beautiful state of hawaii🌺☀️🌈🏝i had 2 babies 18 months apart and i needed to lose the weight. how? prescription diet pills 💊and a low carb/sugar diet. over the years the weight crept back on but i lost it again and got back down to 185lbs in 2009. how? prescription diet pills and a low carb/sugar diet🚫🍩🍪🍰🥪🍟🍚 it’s been an unending battle. why? mentally i hadn’t healed from what was causing me to not love me enough to care about my health. what hadn’t i healed from? childhood trauma of sexual abuse and rape. yep...me too🙋🏽‍♀️ as common as it shouldn’t be it is. and it’s not talked about enough. i’m positive there are millions of women and men like myself that have spent most of their adult lives not truly loving themselves due to some type of trauma from their childhood😔 i’m no therapist or mental health professional, but i do know that the longer you wait to start the journey of healing, the more of your life you will lose. sharing my weight with you all is apart of my healing journey💜i’m taking my life back y’all! and i can only hope this post has inspired and encouraged at least one person to do the same☺️
#mentalhealthmatters #metoo #transparency #weightloss #transformationtuesday #healing #issajourney #plantbased #vegansofig #blackvegan #vegan #vegetarian #starchsolution #carbsarelife #followmyjourney #foodshare #veganfoodshare #whatveganseat #selfcare #healthybody #healthyself #healthysoul #melaninsmoothie

text:
.
استراتژی کارمندان وال استریت برای جلوگیری از متهم شدن به آزار جنسی و از دست دادن شغلشان:
.
با همکاران زن شام نخورید، در پروازها کنارشان ننشینید، اگر‌ با آنها در یک هتل هستید در یک طبقه ی دیگر اتاق بگیرید، از هر‌نوع ملاقات دو نفره(از جمله ملاقات های کاری) خودداری کنید! .
.
.
بعلاوه، یکی از مشاوران وال استریت(wealth advisor) گفته است استخدام زنان یک ریسک غیر قابل پیش بینی به حساب می آید! اگر‌ از حرف ما برداشت بدی کنند چکار باید بکنیم؟
.
.
.
این روش کارمندان وال استریت را به نوعی پیروی از مایک پنس(معاون رئیس جمهور آمریکا) می دانند که وقتی به این‌ مقام رسید گفت از شام خوردن با هر زنی بجز همسرش خودداری خواهد کرد تا احتمال اتهام آزار جنسی را به حداقل برساند.
.
.
سی نفر از مدیران ارشد وال استریت گفته اند از احتمال آزار جنسی وحشت زده اند و احساس می کنند روی پوست تخم مرغ راه می روند.
.
.
پ.ن: بعد از جنبش فمینیستیِ #metoo، زنان در آمریکا و بسیاری کشورهای دیگر این قدرت را دارند که بدون نیاز به مدرک، با طرح اتهام های آزار جنسی مردان را از کار بیکار کنند.
.
.
.
bit.ly/2eccesr
.
.
.
.
.

text:
the sharpshooter has one obsession, one target: marilyn monroe and all that she stands for. he infiltrates our play and marilyn’s life in any way he can. his father taught him to shoot birds, and as an educated, adult man he now excels at being a patient hunter.

he’s been following his prey since 1949, when he took the disguise of photographer otto ose and shot norma’s infamous nudes. she’s in front of a mirror, trembling and animatedly telling marilyn she’s never going to pose naked. marilyn reminds her how easy she was with mr. z, that bills need to be paid. norma gets in front of the camera with her bathrobe on. otto is horny, and pressing, you must be kidding me! take that thing off! b-but i’ve never posed naked before… not naked, nude. not smut, art. there is a crucial distinction. 
_______________

from the script of love is blonde:

the sharpshooter/ otto: you're wearing shoes. take them off. 
norma: please. the floor is so dirty. 
the sharpshooter/ otto: have you ever seen a "nude in shoes"? don't be stupid. 
norma: i don't want to show the bottom of my feet, please. 
the sharpshooter/ otto: the bottom of your feet? 
norma: i don't want you to show... down there. 
the sharpshooter/ otto: what's down there? 
norma: the filth, of the earth. 
marilyn: the filth of the earth? 
the sharpshooter/ otto: hey, this whole game is about money, understand? every piece of your body has to be sold. even your feet. someone will buy 'em. come oooon... little starlet, everything off, now. 
_______________

want to discover more about this mysterious character from our play? support our #crowdfunding today: it’s running until december 14th, and we still have 19,000$ to reach our goal! please contribute any way you can via the #linkinbio: every dollar counts! if we don’t reach the entire goal, we won’t keep any donation, and marilyn’s truth will once again remain untold. 
_______________

text:
*sometimes the days are slow. ⁣
*sometimes the kids are wild.⁣
*sometimes they throw tantrums that down right embarrass you and make you question what the hell your doing being a stay at home mom. ⁣
*sometimes you feel alone even though you have 2 little corsages attached to you all day. ⁣
⁣
*but most of the time i am happy, in love with the most important job there is, being a mom. ⁣
⁣
*today was a “sometimes day” and i felt defeated.  i scrolled through our cali pics and found this.  me and my tantrum throwing beach babe wearing sweaters and suits ready for frozen lemon aid and pool football. the picture is quite ridiculous but it was her idea and it made me smile. ⁣
⁣
*so...tomorrow is a new day.❤️⁣🤞🏼 (i know a lot of you mommas get this⬆️)
⁣

text:
i wanted to share with you about a few events coming up that maybe of interest.  check them out!!
________________
11/13/18 --> the chinese exclusion act: a film screening & discussion: tuesday, november 13th / 6:30pm-8:3pm / mica place (814 n. collington avenue) [link to the facebook event page] [link to the event details on brja's website] [link to eventbrite page]
________________
11/14/18 --> race, racism, and the new racial science with dorothy roberts: wednesday, november 14th / 6pm-8pm / umbc university center ballroom (1000 hilltop circle, 21250) [link to the facebook event page] [link to the event details on umbcs website]
________________
12/1/18 --> hopkins nurses speak out: saturday, december 1st / 10:30am - 12pm / reginald f. lewis museum (830 e. pratt street) (while this may not immediately seem related to racism and racial justice, the couple of nurses i spoke with helping to put this on want to work towards a deeper understanding of how racism impacts both how they are treated at hopkins and how nurses treat their patients and each other) [link to the facebook event page]
________________

pre_proc_tweet:
بنياد بين المللي كر
(كر)یکی از بزرگ‌ترین سازمان‌های امدادرسانی در دنیا است که در سال ۱۹۴۵ در ایالات متحده آمریکا تاسیس شد تا به پناهندگان و آوارگان جنگ جهانی دوم کمک کند. در حال حاضر ماموریت اصلی این بنیاد به میزان قابل ملاحظه‌ای تغییر یافته و بر تعاون و مشارکت برای پایان دادن به فقر در نقاط مختلف دنیا تاکید دارد.
این بنیاد با بیش از ۱۲ هزار نفر کارکنان در ۷۲ کشور دنیا برنامه‌هایی را در دست اجرا دارد. شعب مختلف این بنیاد در آمریکا، انگلیس، ژاپن و هشت کشور دیگر فعال است و تنها در آمریکا بیش از ۳۵۰ هزار نفر اعانه‌دهنده دارد. در سال ۲۰۰۴ شعبه آمریکایی این بنیاد به تنهایی بودجه‌ای معادل ۵۱۷ میلیون دلار برای هدایت ۸۷۰ پروژه کاهش فقر در ۷۰ کشور دنیا هزینه کرد که این پروژه ۴۵ میلیون نفر را پوشش می‌داد. این برنامه اجرای برنامه‌های آموزشی برای یک میلیون دانش‌آموز، کمک به برنامه‌های پیشگیری از ابتلا به ایدز برای ۷ میلیون نفر، کمک به پیشبرد برنامه‌های کشاورزی برای ۵/۶ میلیون نفر و بهبود طرح‌های بهداشتی و سلامت برای حدود ۹ میلیون نفر را شامل می‌شد.
              
   
 
ahmood_rnc

text:
אלימות מגדרית.
קטע שיש נושאים שפשוט קשה לדבר עליהם. זה אולי קורה כי אנחנו יודעים שלא נעשה מספיק לגבי זה והם מוציאים אותנו מאיזור הנוחות שלנו, אולי כי אנחנו לא מכירים אותם מקרוב ואולי כי אנחנו מכירים אותם יותר מדי.
איזו שנה מופלאה של מודעות, מקמפיין #metoo דרך המאבק היום ועם המון תקווה וכוח לגרום לזה לחלחל גם לממשלה שלנו, כי יש תכנית והגיע הזמן להפעיל אותה.
מההיכרות שלי עם כל כך הרבה גברים מדהימים ונשים חזקות אני בטוחה שאנחנו בדרך הנכונה, כי זה לא עניין נשי, זה עניין של החברה כולה.
איזה יום מרגש ועוצמתי ואיזה מאבק צודק!
די, פשוט די לאלימות נגד נשים.
#מצבחירום

i think the difference between being miserable and finding happiness is just a matter of perspective. if you live your life defining yourself by what other people think of you , its a form of self torture. 
let others opinions of you not matter.  let ur own opinion of who you know you truly are matter. if anyone in your life brings more misery to ur life than happiness then it's time for them to go. sometimes it's the hardest thing to do to let go of people who we love or are suppose to love. all i know is if someone doesnt love you right then another human will . one humans trash can be another humans treasure. so let's keep and cherish the treasured ones. when you think you have no one there for you take a look in the mirror. its you. ur there for yourself.  so loving yourself is what matters most to being #happy. #love the beauty & misery cause you overcame struggle . love ur #strength that no one knows or can see. love the special things about you that makes you beautifully unique. #loveyourself even on ur darkest days and i promise light and love waits for you in the happy horizons ❤✌ #perspective#happiness#warrior#fibromyalgia#arthritis#braintumor#amputee#chronicmigraines#degenerativediscdisease#mentalhealth#metoo#mmj#420#710#thc#cbd#maryjane#inspiration#holidays#dontworrybehappy#smile#motivation#staypositive#onelove#staymedicatedneige

text:
jag får fortfarande en hel del mail från både kvinnor och män fast mest är det kvinnor som skriver och berättar. jag fick ett igår från en kvinna jag hade kontakt med för ett år sedan där hon berättade om sin arbetsplats på ett företag i mellansverige med c:a 20 anställda varav 75% män. arbetsmiljön var hemsk. två män lyckades få igång i stort sett alla de andra männen i sexistiska handlingar och kvinnorna kände sig som offer. något som också ledde till intriger, skitprat och vuxenmobbning ibland kvinnorna. hon beskrev en arbetsmiljö helt i avsaknad av moral och etik. när hon skrev till mig för ett år sedan var hon förtvivlad och jag rådde henne att ta kontakt med ett konsultföretag och att börja kriga, bli modig, sätta ner foten och bli besvärlig. du har inget att förlora sa jag till henne. någon måste börja så kommer du garanterat att få dom flesta kvinnorna med dig.

mailet som kom igår var rörande att läsa för hon hade följt mina råd vilket hade lett till att flera blivit uppsagda, fler kvinnor inklusive hon själv blivit befordrade och stämningen på arbetsplatsen gått från skräckvälde till harmoni. -det hade aldrig skett om inte du och cissi och flera andra började svarade hon och då fick jag gåshud av lycka. 
när jag får vinnesmål om att förändringar faktisk sker i vårt avlånga land ser jag ljuset i tunneln och känner hopp om framtiden, hoppet att våra döttrar och söner går en sundare framtid till mötes. hejja er, kämpa på alla ni andra och följ våra råd. ni har inget att förlora och allt att vinna👊🏼✊🏼👊🏼 och glöm aldrig... du är inte ensam!!!! kram och trevlig kväll trots regnvädret. fast imorgon blir det sooool☀️😎☀️ det finns ett fantastiskt ideellt företag som heter @makeequal kontakta dom om du känner igen dig i inlägget, dom kan hjälpa till #metoo #gealdrigupp #nevergiveup💪 @cissiwallin

text:
seit 1999 findet am 25.11. der„international day for the elimination of violence against women“ statt.
es gilt als das größte gesundheitsrisiko für frauen weltweit und allein in deutschland erfahren mehr als 40% der frauen seit ihrem 16. lebensjahr körperliche und/oder sexuelle gewalt. ( quelle:who)
weltweit haben mehr als 15 millionen mädchen zwischen 15 und 19 jahren in ihrem leben bereits sexuelle gewalt erfahren.(quelle:unicef)
je nach gewaltform haben bis zu 80% der betroffenen psychische folgebeschwerden davongetragen.
doch das sind nur vermutungen, die wahre höhe der zahlen ist ein schweigen im raum.
dies gilt es zu brechen.

@lene_kungfu ist schon seit klein auf dabei und trainiert bei uns kungfu und selbstverteidigung. sie ist ein vorbild dafür, das mädchen und frauen sich präventiv schützen können, damit sie selbst die gefahr zu einem minimum reduzieren! 
danke für dein engagement!! die blutrote hand über ihrem mund, schreit nach aufmerksamkeit. es ist wichtig, hinzusehen, hinzuhören und auch mal ohne ersichtlichen bedarf, mal nachzufragen. 
macht mit bei der aktion, sei laut, mach ein selfie und vergiss die rote hand nicht ( egal ob mann oder frau. )
.
.
.

el artista conocido como san-e, es uno de los más famosos de corea, presentándose en programas de televisión y en conciertos.
#san-e​ libera wuooo contra feministas y los internautas obviamente no se hicieron de esperar. en su canción dicen estas palabras: “los hombres son víctimas del confusionismo y el patriarcado, pero ¿por qué?” “hermana ¿por que te enojas? culpa al sistema, no a los hombres” el dice que apoya a las feministas y a la campaña #metoo pero, no lo demuestra en la canción.

les dejamos algunos comentarios:

-[+ 232,-124] san-e, usted tampoco sirvió, entonces por qué usted está llorando sobre las mujeres que no sirven?
-[+ 33,-20] la letra buena

-[+ 24,-23] desde el punto de vista masculino, creó la letra refrescante.... pero me preocupo si sane va a estar bien, ya predigo feminazis atacando. (la traducción era feminazi)
-[+ 22,-9] pero sane tampoco sirvió -[+ 12,-10] está hablando de los hechos ahora. en esta generación, los hombres son más discriminados, mientras que las mujeres reciben todas las ventajas.

text:
do you remember this girl?

she had fear in her eyes but a mission in her heart, she was a victim of a traumatic marriage and a survivor of coercive, physical, financial and psychological abuse. she came out with her story with the intention to help others identify themselves as victims and from a no body she turned into an women’s rights activist and the founder of the broken bride campaign.

my marriage to that man can be best described as being married to a terrorist, he was unpredictable and his narcissistic personality made me loose my inner abilities to make my own decisions and that is why he had so much of a hold on me.

this journey was far from easy but a lesson worthwhile because it turned me into a writer that was able to reach the hearts of those both near and far and today am proud to say that we will be creating waves.

the survivors are appearing from behind closed doors and will appear for the first time on the 8th of december, 2018 at @the_secretgarden to demonstrate that there is nothing holding us back. 
if you haven’t booked your tickets you will be missing out as i will be sharing my secrets and connecting with you on a personal level. •
•
•

text:
@arimelber @donlemoncnn @seanhannity @maddowshow @thejimmydoreshow @cnn @nbcnews wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
tenemos 16 días de activismo contra la violencia de género de este año (del 25 de noviembre al 10 de diciembre) que forma parte de la campaña únete para poner fin a la violencia contra las mujeres es pinta el mundo de naranja: #escúchametambién.

la etiqueta #escúchametambién da protagonismo a las voces de las mujeres y las niñas que han sobrevivido a la violencia, que defienden los derechos de las mujeres día tras día y que pasan a la acción, muchas de las cuales lo hacen lejos de los reflectores o de los titulares mediáticos. son rostros que probablemente no conozcamos de los periódicos y casos de los cuales no hemos oído hablar en los medios sociales.

sus voces y sus opiniones deben ser escuchadas.

una de cada tres mujeres sufre violencia a lo largo de su vida, independientemente de su estatus social, clase, raza, país o grupo de edad. son demasiadas mujeres. para muchas de ellas el momento #metoo todavía no ha llegado, ya que el hecho de expresarse puede tener consecuencias fatales, y la supervivencia es un camino largo y complicado.

actualmente nos encontramos en un punto de inflexión. las conversaciones mundiales de los medios sociales y los movimientos de activistas y sobrevivientes nos han enseñado que cuando nuestras voces se juntan en una, es posible desafiar los desequilibrios de poder históricos e influir en el cambio duradero.

combatir la discriminación y la violencia contra las mujeres y las niñas es un objetivo fundamental del mandato de onu mujeres. por otro lado, sabemos que hay soluciones que pueden promover el cambio transformacional que queremos ver, por ejemplo: un enfoque integral que incluya leyes junto con su implementación decidida para proteger a las mujeres y las niñas ante la violencia, medidas de prevención desde una edad temprana y la prestación de servicios accesibles a todas las sobrevivientes.

text:
@arimelber @donlemoncnn @seanhannity @maddowshow @thejimmydoreshow @cnn @nbcnews wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates suppoed by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

text:
rock - paper - scissors
•
we want to know, would you rather spend money on your spring break/long weekend in march:
a) traveling to a place with a beach (and getting sand in all the wrong places), drinking sugary alcoholic beverages with miniature umbrellas, and having conversations about bathing suits and spf
or
b) spend a few days in the desert and mountains (with a hot tub), surrounded by a tribe of women on a quest to conquer their truth, face their fears, and better the rest of their lives (as well as those around them)?
•
look, there isn’t anything wrong with option a, we’ve been there! but it’s not long term. and the benefit in our opinion doesn’t outweigh the cost. see, we promise to provide you a safe space, an oasis of love and respect, and an opportunity to step into your best life. we want you to have the tools and resources to spike meaningful, powerful, life changing conversations and actions!
•
we’ve got a few more spots open for our retreat in idyllwild, the choice is yours. what’ll it be? rock, paper, scissors, _____________________________.

text:
@arimelber @donlemoncnn @seanhannity @maddowshow @thejimmydoreshow @cnn @nbcnews wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

no, not how you wanted to dress up.
how you needed to dress up.
i have.
do you know why ?
because we live in a world where 100% of women have been a victim of street harassment.

we don’t need to change.
men need to behave ✋🏼

text:
mandag kveld var @pederkjos gjest hos oss i bårstua på skansen. dette var andre episode av min historie. peder leverte varene, enkelt og særdeles greit. det ble en seanse med mange tema og refleksjoner rundt både historie, tiden vi lever i og hvor vi er på vei. papparollen, mannsrollen, livets krav og #metoo. lærerikt og berikende. maten nådde også nye høyder takket være @mayelize og @miniflippersej !
arrangementet var selvfølgelig fullbooket, med venteliste... i ettertid også fullt forståelig. uten å være for svulstig, dette var et av de bedre arrangementene vi har hatt på bårstua. vi takker peder for at han stilte opp på dette. viktig for vi som var der og viktig for fontenehuset i tromsø som får overskuddet! 🤩😍🤑#pederkjøs #jegmotmeg #godpappa #mannsrolle #papparolle #pappa #følelser #tromsø #gamlebyentromsø #skansen #bårstua #kortreistmat #bivrost #aquavit @barstua - det hyggelige møtestedet på skansen foto: @eivinnlarsen

text:
what does sex look like after sexual trauma? @thelilynews contributor katie simon asked seven survivors. ashley says she was sexually assaulted when she was in high school. over the next several years, she struggled to build an enjoyable, meaningful sex life. like many assault survivors, sometimes partners treated her like she was broken, or assumed that she wasn’t interested in sex. many partners treated her as “somebody they needed to be careful with.” as someone who considers herself particularly sex-positive, this was frustrating for her.
•
assault “definitely made me more concerned about the power dynamics behind [sex],” ashley says. “i wanted to be 100 percent in control of sexual experiences after the assault.” she began to prefer approaching partners rather than the other way around. she says, “if you can’t talk about your assault or rape, it’s harder to talk about sex in general.” talking about sexual assault can lead to more open conversations, which can in turn lead to more gratifying sex. (illustration by istock / @thelilynews)

text:
some thoughts on violence prevention from our president and founder yehudit zicklin-sidikman:⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“i dream of a world where i would be able to say to a room full of people, ‘whoever is a survivor, please stand up.’⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
no more hiding. survivors should no longer live in shame. that is the power of #metoo.⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
but this is not enough for me.⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the time has come for us to help reduce the number of survivors of violence by changing how we educate our children and by providing effective tools for dealing  with violence as it is happening.⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
yet in order for there to be fewer survivors in the world, we must demand change.”⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
*⠀
*⠀
*⠀

text:
it’s national & international human rights month, and the #faxx are in: we wanted to let you know that even here, in a developed western country—*still* considered the ‘most powerful’ in the world—a 2015 visit by the un high commissioner led to a report stating that women in the u.s. are significantly lacking in human rights per international standards. yes, since then there have been gains in our government representation; but pay parity, lack of paid family leave and poor health care options and rights were also cited. to move the needle on the sexist bias that f*%#s with our rights—we need to focus on the #faxx: the growing body of statistical evidence, proving power and potential of our contributions to not only raise the status of women but the health, economy and status of our country.
.
.
.
.
.

thank you to the @rankinfund for having me at your house party and for helping me get through my last two semesters at @wpunj.
you have been a blessing to me, many others and i’m sure to many more.”
.

text:
don’t let people tell you what you need, and that beggars can’t be choosers. you didn’t beg them for anything so they can do you both a favor and...
*
keep that 💩
*
you don’t have to be the charity case that strokes their ego. you made it this far in spite of everything thrown at you because you are resourceful and resilient. you don’t mind help but you can do without the condescending handouts.
*
in tomorrow’s email i talk about why it’s important to have standards no matter where you are in life. that is a huge part of self-care. have you joined my email community yet? click the link in the bio to join!
